I really love coming to Sazon Perez Restaurant every time I'm close by. I always get the lunch special which is like $6.50-$7 depending what meat you get and they give you a salad and soda also included. The food is really good, fresh. I unable to go now during breakfast time but I have gone in the past and I was happy to see a large selection of Spanish style breakfast foods. The place is take out only now but it's a small place and only had 3 tables indoors anyway so it not a big change for me. The parking is difficult but it's worth finding to go. Place is usually clean and the staff is super friendly.  They also cater which I have done as well. Good prices. Enjoy!

We always order catering from here for lunch at work.  It is cheap and the portions are ridiculously large.  The food is tasty and they have a variety of dishes.  We usually order the rotisserie chicken, steak, pernil, maduros, maduro stuffed with ground beef and cheese, spaghetti, rice and pigeon peas, and avocado salad.  We always get half trays and even that is too much food.  You can probably feed 50 people and it would only cost you $150.  I especially like the maduro stuffed with ground beef and cheese.  It is so delicious but you might need someone to carry you home.
